text:
Why should a negative times a negative equal a positive? In my experience, students often find it natural when presented as the continuation of a pattern, e.g., 
3 x (-5) = -15
2 x (-5) = -10
1 x (-5) = -5
0 x (-5) = 0
Ask students what comes next. https://t.co/8CBJMBqNh6
